duction - there is minimal referenc</span><span style="font-family:Constantia; font-size:12pt">e to waste heat elimination and</span><span style="font-family:Constantia; font-size:12pt">/or recovery. Greater attention should be given to the possible use of all varieties of heat pumps to deliver waste heat recovery in industrial processes. </span><span style="font-family:Constantia; font-size:12pt">Encourag</span><span style="font-family:Constantia; font-size:12pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Constantia; font-size:12pt">me</span><span style="font-family:Constantia; font-size:12pt">nt should be given to the use </span><span style="font-family:Constantia; font-size:12pt">of newer low temperature heat-to-electric</span><span style="font-family:Constantia; font-size:12pt">ity devices, and planners should</span><span style="font-family:Constantia; font-size:12pt"> be encouraged to prom</span><span style="font-family:Constantia; font-size:12pt">o</span><span style="font-family:Constantia; font-size:12pt">te t</span><span style="font-family:Constantia; font-size:12pt">he use of cascaded waste heat utilisation either from power stations and/or industrial process plant. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">•</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">What progress is t</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">he government making on reducing the demand for heat?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Constantia; font-size:12pt">Not able to comment. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margi